  intro: 'Ukrainian Village\'s block after block of original greystones, brick two-flats, and bungalows on Rice, Iowa, Thomas, and Walton Streets — built between the 1890s and 1920s and among the most architecturally intact historic streetscapes on Chicago\'s West Side — require contractors who understand original roof structures, lime mortar chimneys, and the mixed flat-plus-pitched profiles that define this neighborhood.',
