  metaDescription: 'Roof replacement in River North, Chicago. Converted loft and commercial flat roof specialists, TPO membrane experts, licensed contractors, free estimates.',
  intro: 'River North\'s converted brick warehouse lofts between Chicago Avenue and the river — buildings with 3,000 to 8,000 square feet of open flat roof surface that housed printing plants, cold storage, and light manufacturing before becoming some of Chicago\'s most sought-after residential addresses — now have EPDM and modified bitumen systems installed during the 1990s renovation wave that are well past their useful life.',
  introEs: 'Los lofts de almacén de ladrillo convertidos de River North entre Chicago Avenue y el río — edificios con 3,000 a 8,000 pies cuadrados de superficie de techo plano que albergaron plantas de impresión, almacenamiento en frío y manufactura ligera antes de convertirse en algunas de las direcciones residenciales más buscadas de Chicago — ahora tienen sistemas EPDM y de betún modificado instalados durante la ola de renovación de los años 90 que están bien más allá de su vida útil.',
  areaText: 'River North (ZIP 60654) sits just north of the Chicago River between the Magnificent Mile and the Loop, one of Chicago\'s most densely developed urban districts. The neighborhood transformed from an industrial area into a mixed-use hub of galleries, restaurants, and residential lofts. Building types include converted brick warehouses with large flat roof surfaces, modern high-rise condos, mixed-use commercial buildings, and some smaller townhome developments. Flat roof systems — TPO and EPDM — dominate the older converted warehouse stock throughout River North. High-rise buildings require specialized contractors not on our list. For the warehouse conversions, townhomes, and lower-rise commercial buildings, all six listed contractors have relevant experience. Typical project costs run $10,000 to $25,000 for smaller buildings and $20,000 to $50,000+ for larger warehouse footprints.',
  areaTextEs: 'River North (ZIP 60654) está al norte del río Chicago entre el Magnificent Mile y el Loop. Los almacenes de ladrillo convertidos con grandes superficies de techo plano, condominios modernos y edificios de uso mixto definen el barrio. Los costos van de $10,000 a $25,000 para edificios más pequeños y $20,000 a $50,000+ para almacenes más grandes.',
  faq: [
    { q: 'How much does flat roof replacement cost in River North in 2026?', a: 'Flat roof replacement in River North varies significantly by building size. Smaller converted loft buildings (2,000 to 4,000 sq ft of roof surface) typically run $12,000 to $22,000 for a TPO system. Larger warehouse conversions with 5,000 to 10,000+ sq ft of roof surface run $25,000 to $50,000+. Mixed-use commercial buildings are priced similarly to residential at the same square footage. Free on-site estimates from all six listed contractors.' },
    { q: 'What type of roofing is most common in River North?', a: 'Flat roof systems — predominantly TPO and EPDM — are by far the most common in River North due to the prevalence of converted warehouses and commercial buildings. Most of the flat roofs on converted warehouse lofts were installed 15 to 25 years ago and are now at or approaching end of life. Standing seam metal roofing is also present on some newer mixed-use buildings. High-rise glass curtain wall buildings have their own specialized systems not handled by our listed contractors.' },
    { q: 'What is the best flat roof system for a River North converted warehouse loft?', a: 'TPO membrane is the strong recommendation for River North converted warehouse lofts. Large flat roof surfaces benefit especially from TPO\'s heat-welded seams — on a 5,000 square foot roof, the difference between welded and adhesive seams at every joint is significant over 25 to 35 years. TPO also reflects summer heat, reducing cooling costs on top-floor loft units that can be substantial in uninsulated warehouse structures. Your contractor will measure the exact roof area and propose the appropriate membrane thickness and warranty.' },
    { q: 'Do River North contractors work on commercial buildings?', a: 'Yes. All contractors on our list handle both residential and light commercial flat roof replacement in River North. Mixed-use buildings — ground floor commercial with residential above — are common in this neighborhood and all listed contractors have experience with them. For large purely commercial buildings (office buildings, hotels), call to confirm that the project scope falls within the contractor\'s residential and light commercial service area.' },
    { q: 'Site access in River North is tight. How do contractors manage material delivery?', a: 'River North\'s narrow streets and dense parking are a standard logistical challenge that local contractors manage routinely. Most use delivery trucks with cranes or conveyor systems to bring materials to the roof, and schedule deliveries during off-peak hours to minimize street impact. Your contractor will confirm the access plan during the free estimate and note any parking or street access fees in the written scope.' },
    { q: 'Is a permit required for roof replacement in River North?', a: 'Yes. Chicago requires a building permit for all full roof replacements in River North including commercial and mixed-use buildings. All listed contractors pull this permit as part of every project. For commercial buildings, the permit process may include an additional structural review step. River North\'s active commercial real estate market means unpermitted roof work creates significant title and insurance complications — never work with a contractor who suggests skipping the permit.' },
  ],
