  areaText: 'Jefferson Park (ZIP 60630) is a Far Northwest Side neighborhood anchored by the Jefferson Park Transit Center — a major Blue Line and bus hub on Milwaukee Avenue at Lawrence. Home to generations of working-class and middle-class Chicago families, predominantly Polish-American and more recently Latino. The housing stock is primarily Chicago bungalows and brick two-flats built between 1920 and 1950, with some larger apartment buildings near the transit corridors. The residential streets — Foster, Berteau, Sunnyside, and Winnemac off the main corridors — have the classic bungalow belt housing defining the neighborhood. Many homes are on their second roofing cycle. Typical costs run $8,000 to $13,000 for bungalows and $8,000 to $14,000 for two-flat flat roofs.',
