  intro: 'Chatham\'s brick bungalows and two-flats on Langley, St. Lawrence, and Wabash — block after block of well-maintained properties between 75th and 87th Streets that represent one of Chicago\'s longest traditions of Black homeownership — are predominantly on 1990s roofs that have reached or exceeded the 25-year lifespan of asphalt shingles in Chicago\'s climate and are ready for planned replacement.',
